Paper: hep-th/0212139

Date: 2002-12-12

Title: Singularity Resolution in Gauged Supergravity and Conifold Unification

Authors: J. D. Edelstein, A. Paredes, A. V. Ramallo

Comments: 13 pages, harvmac, one figure; v2

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B554 (2003) 197-206

We obtain a unified picture for the conifold singularity resolution. Wepropose that gauged supergravity, through a novel prescription for thetwisting, provides an appropriate framework to smooth out singularities in thecontext of gravity duals of supersymmetric gauge theories.